product_name: AMDRO Kills Fire Ants Yard Treatment Bait 5lb
review_title: About 80% effective and appears to work seasonally
review_text: First off, I use about 25lbs of Amdro every year on my farm, so Im speaking from experience. Its great when it works but not all fire ants (and look alike ants) were created the same.My first observation is this stuff always works if you get enough bait on and around the mound and the ants accept it as food. I usually disturb a mound and the sprinkle bait on the mount and around it to get bait out in the feeding zone about a foot outside of the mount perimeter.The ants rarely accept the bait in early Spring so wait until the ground warms up enough to plant corn.About 80% of the ant hill colonies will see the bait as food and can be seen moving the particles of Amdro into the nest. I have seen as much as a quarter cup of the bait disappear in about 20 minutes on some mounds. The other 20% wont touch the stuff, and there is where a different approach is needed.I have tried using a rake handle to poke a hole in the mound to allow me to pour Amdro into the hole. The theory being the ants will repair the nest and have to contend with the material in doing so, maybe deciding to eat it. That approach has had sporadic success but by no means 100%. I still have to use Bifenthrin on the stubborn hills.Bottom line, it only takes one grain of this material to kill the colony, if the ants accept it as food and if they feed it to the queen(s). Note that some colonies have more than one queen.

Brand doesnt matter, itll all work. Put that on top of this stuff.4) drizzle JUST A LITTLE honey on top of the concoction youve made. This stuff is good, but the little critters seem to need a little encouragement to get to the pile.5) wait 3 days. Celebrate your victory.Lemme explain whats happened. This magical stuff attracts the ants, they grab it and take it home and accidentally commit ant genocide. BUT WAIT THERES MORE. The diatomaceous earth you spread out is so fine that its small enough to work its way inside the ants exoskeleton. SO in addition to poisoning the little devils, youve destroyed them mechanically from the inside. BOOM. Take that Flik, hopper aint got nothing on me! *insert maniacal laughing here*

product_name: AMDRO Kills Fire Ants Yard Treatment Bait 5lb
review_text: This any killer never fails me. Easy to apply with gloved hand around aunt beds or can be broadcast. I trickle some of the yellow granules around a bed of ants. The ants love the taste and immediately start picking it up and taking it into the hive. Inside the hive the ants and their queen eat this stuff up. Hours later, the granules kill the ants. Sneaky trick - formulated for the ants to accept it, as it initially does not harm them. But, then it does its deadly job. Fantastic product.
